-- Peru’s Cofide Hires Banks to Set Up Meetings With Bond Investors
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2012-01-26T16:32:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/peru-s-cofide-hires-banks-to-set-up-meetings-with-bond-investors.html
Corporacion Financiera de Desarollo
SA, Peru’s state development bank, hired Deutsche Bank AG and
JPMorgan Chase & Co. to arrange meetings with bond investors,
according to a person familiar with the discussions.  Cofide, as the bank is known, will meet investors starting
tomorrow in  Europe ,  Latin America  and the U.S., said the person,
who declined to be identified because terms aren’t set. A dollar
bond sale may follow, according to the person.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  